\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid14497673 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You were saying your father was definitely working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well, yes. But he was probably rather different to the average 
working class at that time. For instance, on his bookshelf I can remember, you know, Shakespeare, Thomas Hood, Pope, Chaucer, and all that sort of thing, which you wouldn't have gone into the ordinary working class family and found.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. Not today either, or in a middle class home often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And we were Socialists almost as soon as we could toddle, because it was expected in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Tell me what your father's job was when he first went to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, sorry, no. Let's go back a bit further than that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Can you tell me what you know about your father's own family and his early life before you came into it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well, my grandfather, he was a cabinet maker and they had a shop at the bottom of the high street, and he used to make furniture, y
ou know, home made furniture business and that sort of thing. And then he stopped doing that and then took on a small holding and did market gardening. That was my grandfather on my father's side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 This was shall at Halstead, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And my father, as I said before, was an iron moulder at the local foundry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Did he start off like that, was that his first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 As far as I know, on that I'm not altogether certain, but I think he was, all the time I was conscious of it he was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Do you know if your Grandmother, your father's mother, had had any job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I'm afraid I don't know, not on his side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. And your mother, herself, did she have a job before she married and had a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I can only guess that before she was married she must have been because everybody had to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And what do you think she would have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I'm afraid I don't know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. Do you think it might have been domestic service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 It could have been, I couldn't day. I just don't kn
ow. But I know that granny, me mum's mother, at the age of eight used to have to do straw collecting and had to do so much a day before she was released from it. That would be a farmer no doubt. And this osier dealer which I spoke about, you know, draw on
 the osiers who like a crotchet stick. And that was my mother's mother and that's really about all I know about her, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And can you tell me how it was that your father first got interested in socialism?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I don't know. But there was quite 
a progressive liberal group in Halstead as far back as I can remember. There was about half a dozen people in the town and we were an Independent Labour Party, and I can remember leaving school and going sweeping out the little club room that they had, yo
u know. We would have a little treat once a year at Christmas, you know, a bag of sweets for the children. It was just a little group of progressive men in the town. And so we were almost brought up with a socialist leaning you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Did your father talk much to you about socialism and what it meant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Not directly. We just soaked it up I suppose, you know. And possibly a question of elections. And as I told you before he was like a first labour county councillor on the Essex County Council, and I can remember him going off in pony and trap to speak at 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5709250\charrsid11999024 Colne E}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 ngaine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5709250\charrsid11999024 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024  Grinstead Green in his election campaign.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. What year was that? Do you remember, him going off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I should think that would be in the region of 1920. I'm not certain of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You were saying you thought that you were a bit better off than some families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Yes. 'Cos my father used to have these polyphones in the village public houses. He had a couple in Great day, one in the Chequers and one in the Eight Bells, and various
 villages, and then go and collect the money in pony and trap, you see, perhaps once a month or whatever it was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Can you describe how these polyphones were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, well \{BLANK\} and they stood about this high (that was about nearly {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname metricconverter}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname ProductID}{\xmlattrvalue 6 foot}}}6 foot{\*\xmlclose}) with a g
lass front and a big round metal disc with holes to pluck them, they'd pluck like a dulcimer arrangement. Quite pleasant music, you know. There was about ten records on then you'd set the thing, you're your penny in, and you got this music out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 (Was it the same thing as the pianola?)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. He used to have pianolas as well, which they had a roll almost like mutton cloth with pins in and he had some of those too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 (I've seen a pianola.)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 He had some of those too, yes, in the village public hou
ses. And he used to do a certain amount of dealing. He'd buy stuff, we hadn't a shop like, but he'd got in with firms in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. He'd actually sold pianos and that sort of thing like. He could get money that way. He sold the first gramophones in Halstead. 
And took one on one occasion to Ye Old Wagon and Horses, and when they heard the voice on this gramophone record they just couldn't believe it and insisted there was someone under the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 When he did this dealing, did he do it from the house, sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 From the house, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, and can you tell me exactly what his main job sort of involved, and what the work actually was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 We}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5709250\charrsid11999024 ll, iron moulder. You make mould}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 s in the sand and pour in molten metal cast iron, you see, to produce castings. In his case he did mostly those tops of the old tortoise stoves, he used to make those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 What was the firm called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Tortoise Foundry Company. Courtways. Lots of people would remember them. They're still in existence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And did he have any particular rank or file? Was he a foreman or anything of that type?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And, going back to your father again, how much education did he have? I mean, how old was he when he left school, do you know?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I don't know, but I should think about twe
lve years old, I should think. Then I'm only guessing. I mean, you could probably get more accurate information.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And did he have any kind of courses or education after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not to my knowledge, except that he read a tremendous lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And when would he read, would it be in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Yes, between ten and one o'clock in the morning. Ten o'clock at night and one o'clock in the morning. We'd both sit and read and we had to read something if it was only comic cuts, he'd take something from me but he had to read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And you mentioned several authors. You mentioned Thomas Hood, I can't remember any of the others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Chaucer, Shakespeare, they were always on the bookshelf.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, and he read them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, he read them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 'Cos you know in many houses they are on the bookshelf but they're not read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, he read everything he could lay his hands on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Did he read socialist literature too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh yes, he would have done. And I think he was active in, oh what did the
y call them, free thinkers. And my older sisters used to go to school and come out from scripture or enter after scripture, and later in the afternoon if there was any more scripture they had to walk out, which they didn't particularly like, but he insist
ed because he belived that you should have the right not to do that. Not necessarily because it was wrong, because we all went to Sunday School, in any case, but he did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Do you think it was perhaps because he felt religion ought not to be taught in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well that would be in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Church{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} in that time, and he would have objected on principle to the children being subjected to it willy milly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, I see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 He was probably atheist himself, certainly agnostic, but he didn't object to us going to Sunday School or anything of that sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. But if you yourself had objected to going to Sunday School what do you think his attitude would have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 He wouldn't have objected. He would never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 He wouldn't have minded you not going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And did he ever go to Church himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 What religion had he been brought up to, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 None I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 None at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 None to my knowledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. He'd never been Church of England or Congregationalist or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 It would have been Congregationalist if anything, it's where we went to and he never objected to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. But don't you know what his own parents views had been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No I'm afraid I don't
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. And what about your mother, did she have any religion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. Not officially I don't think, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. Didn't she go to a place of worship either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. For one thing she'd never have time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. But do you know if she had feelings of, you know, principle about religion and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I don't think she was agnostic at all, or otherwise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. But your parents were more or less in agreement in their views on religion? This is really what I'm getting at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. To my knowledge. I never heard them discuss religion.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. It wasn't discussed in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Do you remember being conscious that your parents views and attitudes to religion was different to other people's parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. Among the children you knew when you were a child did most of their parents go to Church or Chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I should say quite a lot did, I mean, you'd say that because well, the Church is well forward\'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 In the countryside in the country villages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, and there were lots of people who did go to church and chapel in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But you don't ever remember feeling odd or out of it or different because your parents didn't go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not in church sense, no. Politically, perhaps, yes. If I might divert?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, do, how did that affect you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
I can remember going to school and there was an election, you know, liberal and tory. And the boys were floating their rosettes and chiding me because I hadn't one. And I asked for one and was sent with a red one. And "What is that?
" "Oh, that's a socialist." "Well there is no such thing." You know, and in that sense I was an odd man out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And did they sort of argue with you about socialism and this kind of thing, the other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not really argue. Really we weren't capable of arguing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. Were there other boys in the school with parents with these views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, there was another fellow, his parents were also part of this I.R.P. and he was at school at the same time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Was he a friend of yours in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not a particular friend but just as if you grow up in Halstead together you always know each other.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. What about your sister and her experience of having to withdraw from scripture like that? Did you have to do similarly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No because I went to the state school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I see, yes, but they presumably had scripture there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 They had scripture.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But your father didn't object?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No, they, well that was mostly, you see he thought that was right for people to be able to opt out and having
 fought for it and believed in it then he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5709250\charrsid11999024 felt he should follow his convic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 tions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But it was particularly because of church schools that he felt this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes this was a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Church{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, I see. And did you have any other brothers and sisters besides the sister you mentioned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. I had three older sisters, two older brothers, and I had a younger sister and a younger brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 So there were eight of you in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And when you were born, can you tell me the year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 1903.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, approximately how old were your parents when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I've no idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well would you say nearer 30 or nearer 40, would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I should have to guess, mind, but they must have been nearer 40 I should think. I'm not sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
It doesn't matter. It's not an important question, I just wondered if you had a rough idea. And can you tell me something about the house you lived in when you were a child? What was it like? What type of house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Just an ordinary six roomed, li
ke a three bedroom, a sitting room or a front room, you know, and a living room kitchen or scullery we used to call it, where the washing was done and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And was it a terraced house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.. It belonged to the Co-op actually. There again my father was on the committee of the Co-op and seemed to be almost all my life.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, and do you know what the rent was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 7/6 or 8/-. I'm only guessing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, it was a weekly rent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. It's difficult this when you're a youngster. You've not really got an idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No of course not. It's not really important. When you were a young child did you spend much time with your father in a companionable way?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not much because he was out every evening, because he had committees and all this thi
ng, so it was always dressing and going out every evening. So we didn't got much time. But occasionally we'd sit, as I got a little older, we'd sit reading and we used to look at one another to see who was going to bed first, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. All the others would have gone to bed, would this be just the two of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Yes. And on rare occasions we'd stop and talk religion, but very rarely. And he'd never, if I argued with him, try to take a religious attitude. He would answer back, but not forcibly, he'd try to avoid it really. Not to influence me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 He tried not to influence you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 He stayed his point, but never forcibly, he'd never really go out of his way to argue with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And when you read, did you discuss what you were reading? Do you remember? And talk about the books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No, not often.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Did your mother read? She presumably had very little time, if any? I just wondered if you did remember her reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I don't remember her really settling down to read, unless it was a daily newspaper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. You got a daily paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
We had the 'Daily Herald'. It was the exception. And she would read about Ramsay MacDonald and kind of worshipped Ramsay MacDonald and she died before he let her down, or I think she would have been broken hearted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Why do you think she had such a particular feeling for him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Because he represented out point of views, she said, you know. He was the man for the working class. As we had been brought up to believe in the labour party, and that sort of
 thing, you see. In him the first labour prime minister then I think we all had great faith in him. She died before things went wrong with Ramsay MacDonald and Jimmy Carson those people\'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Sold out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Sold out as we felt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And did she go out at night to any meetings or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Very occasionally she'd go across, along the road to the public house and back for half pint of beer, with one or two neighbours, that probably was her only recreation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. What would the neighbours be? Women friends or another couple?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
They would be women neighbours and they'd just meet and probably make half a pint of stout last them, say, all the evening. They never had all the evening to spare really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. But on committees and things of that type she didn't play an active part?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
She didn't play an active part in that sense, but always tried to make things easier for me father to do his, in the sense of ironing his cuffs, or ironing his shirt collar, you know, when he was going out to various meetings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 She was behind him in his work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 She was behind him, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And do you think they talked about it much, the various works?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh yes, I think they would have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And did your father have any jobs in the house or garden at all that he did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Oh, in the garden. We had a very big garden, vegetable garden, which was essential. And he'd work on the garden and we all had to work on the garden, and we had a few chicken.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 The girls too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well not particularly the girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But the boys worked on the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But did he have any indoor tasks to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. Not in the same sense that I have to do the washing up and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Did you have any indoor jobs to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, this is what I had to do, as I think I 
told you before, Saturday mornings we had to clean the knives on a board with what we called brick bat, you know, we had to do that. Or fetch a half-hundred weight of coal, perhaps for ourselves or for a neighbour, and be offered a bit of bread and jam as
 compensation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Did you have any others? Boot cleaning, any regular jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 They wouldn't let me clean the boots for the family as I remember. 'Course the girls would have their chores, looking after some of us.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, and did they help your mother with her housework, the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 They would have done, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And did your mother, I mean did anybody else, relatives or friends, help her at all with the work in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No I don't think so. Everybody was so fully occupied.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Do you remember her getting any help at all from neighbours about anything really?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Well neighbours. The neighbour next door, as I said, mother used to have to go to work at the factory at six o'clock in the morning until six o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Now you told me last time, but I've forgotten, the exact sort of facts about it; over what period of her life did she do that work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 If she was working until, soon after I was been she did finish at the factory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And I think you said you were either fifth or sixth in the family, I'm not sure which you said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I was sixth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, so she was doing that work when she had six children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, although one of them were not her children, one was a half-sister of mine which she brought up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes and did she do, do you know if she did the work pretty continuously throughout that period of having children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Have you any idea of how much time she would take off when she was expecting a baby and after it was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I don't know exactly because I wouldn't have been in the know about that sort of thing. But you can be assured it wouldn't be long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. And she would go out to work about what time in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Quarter past six and getting into work at six - sorry, quarter to six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Quarter to six to get to work at six, yes. As to take you through the day, as it were, can you tell me, she'd go off then, then what would the rest of the family do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 The older sisters then would have to take if not me the other children out to some woman to be looked after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 She would take the younger children somewhere, that would be the children who weren't at school would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 The children who were not at school had to be taken to some woman or other who would look after us and 
that and she had to pay them half-a-crow a week. Sometimes she would work all the week and not get any money to ta on a Friday night because if they didn't finish a piece of cloth, she used to do this fine silk then, and if you didn't finish a roll or wha
tever they called it, you had no money to take, but you still had this half crown to pay to this woman for looking after the children.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You mean if you didn't finish it you had no money at all that week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No money at all that week. It would come on to the next week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You would get more the next week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Then you would get more if you finished the roll. But you didn't get paid unless you finished it, this roll of silk or whatever it was weaving.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I understand. And what would she then do about the woman to whom she owed the money for the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 She paid the half crown I suppose and had to wait until the next week for her money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And do you remember anything about that person you were taken to? Do you have any memories of her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And of course my older brothers and sisters went through the same process you see, of being taken out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And I think you mentioned that your sister said at what age you were taken. Do you know what age you went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Well I suppose quite young. They used to say I crawled about in the cinders and I've heard it remarked that father said one day as I was brought home once, he looks as if he's brought up on cinders and mocks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You don't really know though anything about her, what sort of care she gave you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. Not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And you haven't heard what she was like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well sister said she was only allowed one child and she thinks she was reasonable for those times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 So presumably you were brought up on a bottle by her, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Sorry I can't answer that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
To take us back to the early mornings when your mother had gone off your sister would take you to the person who looked after you and that would be first thing would it be about six o'clock you'd go up there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Probably before they went to school, you see, they would take me or the other ones then go off to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 What time did school start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 About nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, and did you have anything to eat before you went off then, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And was there breakfast in the family? Was breakfast a meal at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Oh yes. There used to be a factory stop of three-quarter hour and there would be a breakfast and come home to breakfast, three-quarter hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes and your father would do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Father would come home and mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And would she then serve up the breakfast when she came home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Would she have prepared it before hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Probably prepared it beforehand, overnight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Can you remember what it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well we'd have porridge, I can remember that and\'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 What type of porridge, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Quaker Oats I think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Quaker Oats? I just wondered 'cos some people still used the old fashioned type at that time, you know, the slow cooking type.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 This was slow cooking it wouldn't be Quick Quaker Oats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. Not the flattened oats, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. I mean Quaker Oats is just the name that comes to my mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes I understand. And what did you have on your porridge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Probably sugar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, and did you have any milk to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not to drink as such, you may have had a little milk on your porridge but that would have been all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, and did you have anything else for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 We probably had an egg as we kept chickens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 A whole egg would you have had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Father would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, but what about the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Probably half an egg or sometimes the top off me father's egg.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Did you have bread or anything else like that with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes we had bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And did you have tea with your breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And when breakfast was done, what did your mother do about the dishes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I don't know, but I should guess the older girls would wash them up. I'm only guessing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, and she wou
ld then have had to go back. She would have had three-quarter hour would she? And in that three-quarter hour she also had to go to and from her work in that period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 How long was her journey to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 About 8 or 9 minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 8 or 9 minutes, yes. So she probably had not much more than half an hour really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Less than half an hour, about 20 minutes, at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And then you'd go off to school, and, well the older children would take you off. And then when would
 the family be together again? At the midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Midday, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Which was what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I think it was 1.0 - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname metricconverter}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname ProductID}{\xmlattrvalue 2.0 in}}}
2.0 in{\*\xmlclose} those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 They'd have an hour off would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 An hour off, 'cos they'd work 'til six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Did they have an hour at the mill as well as at the foundry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. I think so. And..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And when she came back then would there be anybody in the house doing work for her while she was out? Or was the housework just left?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 The housework would be left. But as regards
 the meal she'd have had to prepare the vegetables and pudding and whatever it was, you see, overnight. Get them all ready on the stove and the neighbour would come in and put them on the kitchen range, put them on the fire at the appropriate time so that
 when she got home they would be cooked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Do you know if this was a favour done by the neighbour or was she paid for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I don't think she was paid for it, but I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. And was it always the same type or meal everyday, something sort of cooked on the stove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Oh we usually had a cooked meal, mostly with plenty of vegetables and perhaps rather stodgy food by our standards, you know, suet puddings, meat puddings, um, and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Did you have meat every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
I couldn't remember. We'd, sometimes we'd have what we called pease soup, and again what we'd call a shine bone, with split peas and lentils and made into a soup with dumplings.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 If you had that would you perhaps not have meat for that meal do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Probably not. Another meal, which we used to have, which is typical {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Essex{\*\xmlclose}
, was what they called baked sticking and potatoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 That would be liver, with various offal, with dumplings put in and potatoes all in a dish and the
n covered with a sheet of this membrane stuff that you might see on still, you know what I mean, this fatty skin part of the inside of the animal, you see, which would give a sort of shield from the heat and fatty and that would constitute almost a whole 
meal, you see, with your vegetables and potatoes and dumplings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Did you ever start the meal with a pudding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 When you talk about pudding, do you mean a sweet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No, I mean Yorkshire pudding, or any kind of boiled pudding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, Yorkshire pudding, yes we'd start the meal with that. That'd be a separate course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Yes. Were there any other kind of puddings you'd have in your family as a separate course, 'cos sometimes you used to have it nearly every day, a separate pudding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. It could be a suet pudding, you see, which you might have with gravy or jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. To start the meal as a first course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And if you had it to start the meal you wouldn't have any kind of sweet pudding to follow the meal, presumably, would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 More often that not we didn't have a sweet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Whatever you had for first course you\'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 That was mostly the meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. The meat and the vegetables and that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Very occasionally we had what we called }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2959092\charrsid11999024 mellow}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024  sweet(?), but that was the exception.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. What about Sundays? Did you have anything special on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Little bit of lamb on Sundays, a joint cooked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And a pudding usually on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, usually a Yorkshire pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And a sweet on Sundays or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, I should say we'd probably get a sweet on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Then at dinner did you have any tea or anything like that to drink with your meal, I mean at dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, at dinner. No I should think not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And did you have grace? Presumably not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And then after you'd had the meal what would happen to the clearing of the table and the dishes and all that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I don't know really, but probably my mother would whisk them out into the kitchen, or we used to call it the wash-house in thos
e days, and whether the older girls would wash 'em up when they came out of school, or probably left them 'til night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And your mother would then go back to the mill and would you have come home for that meal when you were a child, you know, with 
the child minder, do you know? Or do you think you stayed there the whole day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I should think I'd stay there the whole day. I don't really know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 We were saying that she had to hurry to take the smaller children back from the person who was lookin
g after them back to the home for the midday meal. And I have heard your sister in law say that your mother was so tired she's seen her standing for sheer weariness just standing at the table with her elbows on the table completely and utterly exhausted. 
So I mean she must have had a terribly grinding day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
I think there was really no let up for her, how would you say, when she came home in the evening to do a heavy day's washing after all this in the mill and looking after the family.
 It just wore her out. I mean being a woman she'd hear it from her and the woman had heard it from the other women in the family.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. So you did probably come back then for the midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, then those that were presumably at school went back to school in the afternoon. And when did your mother's work day finish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 At six o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 At six o'clock, and so was your tea then when she came back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And did your father come back at more or less that time too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 So that you all had tea together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And can you remember then what that meal consisted of, and how it was served?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I suppose it was mostly bread and jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. You don't remember having anything extra with it at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. We
ll when we were getting lettuces and say stuff from the gardens we would probably have that, you see. 'Cos we did have this garden, so anything that had been got on the garden we would have. And an occasional tin of salmon, perhaps, or something of that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Did your mother do any bottling or pickling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 She would have made jam and that sort or thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 She would have found time for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 She would have had to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. When do you think she did that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, in the evening, or at weekends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And then when she'd served the tea, would she, what would happen then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
If it was Monday, she would have to light the copper fire and she'd have to do the family washing and no washing machine of course, but merely the scrubbing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 After a day's work!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And through an old mangle, and it had to be done, there was no other time to do it, unless she did it weekends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And where did she put the things to dry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, we had a long garden, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But during the winter it would have been dark then, would she have hung them out, do you know if she ever hung them out at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I don't remember. She might possibly have left them 'til the next day and put them out at breakfast time or the neighbour hung them out, 
or anything, I don't remember, those details, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. This is very interesting to me because, in now she managed. What about, do you ever remember her doing ironing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And that, would she do that the following night, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Probably, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 What sort of time then do you think she stopped her work in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I should think about ten o'clock and went to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 'Cos when you talked about your father and his reading from ten o'clock 'til one, that would probably be after her\'85 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 After she'd gone to bed. 'Cos this was when I was a bit older of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. About what sort of age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, eighteen, perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. What about things like the beds being made? When were they done, and who did them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
I should think my mother did them. Possibly some of my older sisters but I should think my mother did them. You see she wouldn't do much in the dinner hour but when she got home at night.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 The boys and your father, you didn't make your own beds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And what about the washing up? You say your father didn't help with the washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Did the boys help with that at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not the boys. You see there were two or three older sisters and they probably done it, not involved in th
at, I couldn't swear to that, but I'm almost sure they most certainly would have done it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And cleaning the house, was that also in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Must have been. No other time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Because did she work a full day on Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No, it would be half day on Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Which was six 'til twelve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 'Til one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Mending in the evening too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Your wife said just now about how she heard about her weariness feeling, or seeing, or hearing her talk about how she felt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
She wouldn't often talk about it, but as I got older I could see and knew that she was really tired out. She did finish up with the doctor saying that she'd got a tired heart, you know, and she literally was worn out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. What sort of age do you think you were when you began to realize what she was going through?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, probably I was well over 21.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 The neighbour that came in to put the dinner on, presumably she didn't go to the mill to work? No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No, I don't think she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Did quite a lot of the mothers of the children you knew go down to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, I think a lot of them did, but then again, as a child you are not conscious of what's going on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No, of course not. Can you remember when you went to school what you would do in the school holidays when your mother was at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Well in the August holidays we'd go and pick blackberries up in the wood. Go down to the river and paddle and that sort of thing, you know. Probably do little chores, as I say, get l-cwt of coal or something of that sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And would you be at home quite a lot of the time though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And she presumably wasn't there or did they have some holiday time off when the children were at home in the holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Well they didn't have time off and yet I can't really remember being there on my own. But it was soon after I was born, you see, that she did pack up this factory job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Course she did, yes. So you think that, in fact, what age were you actually when 
you went to school 'cos children start at different times in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}England{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and at different ages too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Three or four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Three or four, yes. And do you think she'd stopped work by then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 So of course she probably would have been around the house while you were home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Did she do any baking of any kind, bread or otherwise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Occasionally, but not much bread, mostly in the way of cakes and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, The regular bread of the family was bought was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes I think so.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Was that her only recreation of going to the pub with a couple of neighbours occasionally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Yes. And on a Sunday evening, we'd walk sometimes, the family would go for a walk to Greenstead Green, to a village about three miles off, walk
 through the meadow and the children would sit on the green while the parents went into the public house. We'd have, say, a bottle of ginger beer and a packet of crisps and that was really a great treat. And I can remember vividly walking down the lane, I
've taken the wife down these lanes, and snapping these what we called 'shirt buttons', these little flowers, you know, they have these seeds, you know, just snapping these little 'shirt buttons', but we were perfectly happy on those things, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Would you do that in the summer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Most Sundays would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh no. Not every Sunday, but occasionally when several of the family got together and we'd have this walk through the fields.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Would their be other relations along too, with you, or just your own particular family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh there might be one or two families join up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Did your mother have relations near at hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not on her side, no. Only father's relations and her own particular family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Your mother's mother lived at Ash Green.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Yes, Ash Green, that's about a couple of miles up the road and she would walk into town about twice a week, perhaps, and then bring us a little bag of sweets, or something. She must bring something, or comic cuts, you see. But that was th
e only relation near at hand that I think me mother hand. She did have an old uncle who lived at Coppersfield but rarely had contact.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 There were two children after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 How old were you when the next one was born, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 About two years difference I think, I'm not absolutely sure.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 About two years, yes. And the one after that, about two years do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. But I'm only guessing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 (Your sister would be 59 and your younger brother is 61)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 So it was about three years and then two years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh it wasn't that, I'm 65 now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 (Yes, but you see you were 65 and your brother is over 60.)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And there's Beat comes between.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 (Oh it's Beat comes between, so that's Beat that's 61you're your brother is 59 or 60.)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
That's better. (So there would have been an interval or 4 years nearly between you and the next one, and then between that one and the last one there would have been an interval of 2 years. So it was 4 and then 2.)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 4 and then 2. And I wo
ndered if you remembered how your mother managed when her last children were born, you know. Presumably they were born at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh yes, they were born at home. No, I'm afraid I don't remember exactly. I can remember my young brother being born and all
 that went with it, but just what happened I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You don't know whether she had a midwife or a doctor or..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I should think not. I'm only guessing, she probably had a doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Did she have, even women who were poor in those days, q
uite often had someone to come in and help them in the house sometimes even more than today actually in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, help them in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 They often tended to have, the usual thing in those days was for women to stay in bed longer, all classe
s that was, actually I wondered if anyone came in and helped her with her work at that time when the two youngest were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I should think the older sisters would have done.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You think the older sisters did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 That was something 
I should have asked you earlier. Well perhaps Mrs. Spurgeon can sort of, I mean, what the ages of the older children were when you were born, actually what the gaps were between you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well the one above me was a brother and he would have been 2 or 3 years older than me because he went in the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Now when you were four, approximately four, you think, you went to school. Can you tell me anything about this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well my first recollections are inclined to be, to school, was having a little sq
uare of zip, and we had to pull this zip away from straights. I can only think the purpose of that was just to get your fingers manipulating. I can't think of any other purpose and that's my first impression of school and not much else at that stage.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No..You don't remember anything about being taught to read and write?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Oh, I can remember, you know, as I got older. I can't actually remember, actually learning to write, but we sort of glowed through these periods you know, until in the latter end, w
hich would be run into the war, you see, and then in 1916 at the age of 13 on my 13}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
 birthday I left and started work at 6 o'clock in the morning. But had I stayed on 'til 14, which it was then, but there was a rule came out in the war that if an employer
 wanted someone and he approached the headmaster and the parents, then that child could leave, because they wanted the labour. And the male teachers had been taken off into the war any way, so we seemed to be marking time, so I left at 13. My parents said
,
 when I went home, "Mr. Rayner had been here and would you like to work there? You please yourself whether you go or not, or carry on at school." I said yes, thinking how lovely it would be to roam around the countryside on horse and cart, which I did enj
oy to a certain extent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And you had no wish to stay on longer at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No, but since then I've struggled with the W.E.A. and been attending lectures for the last 47 years to try and catch up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And if you had stayed on at school, had you passed standard 7?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. Standard 6, I think was the highest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Was that the highest you were able to go at that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I think so.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 If you had stayed on, would you actually have learnt anything more do you think at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I don't think 
I should have learned much because the men teachers had gone and we were over crowded and that sort of thing. But we had a wonderful headmaster, a Mr. Matthews, who used to read to us from the classics. He'd get a few of us in the playground and read from
 
the classics. He was a wonderful man, and he had pictures put in the National Gallery, yes that's right, the Royal Academy, and we'd get a half day off when he'd done a picture for the Royal Academy. And he was a really wonderful man. He loved his Shakesp
eare and, not that I was so conscious of it then, but then as I knew him after that he was an exceptional headmaster and had I stayed he could have probably got me more interested in the arts and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Do you remember what particular classics, you mentioned Shakespeare, did he read from Shakespeare to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
He probably read some Shakespeare, but he'd read Pickwick Papers perhaps, or the Water Babies, not that I remember much about that. I'm a bit confused being only twelve then, I can't say rea
lly for sure what they were, but after leaving school and heard him read his Macbeth and that, and he always, whenever he went on holiday, took a pocket edition of Macbeth. He was a really wonderful man and we had two good men, but the other one was taken
 into the Army. He was a Quaker and he eventually joined the medical corps, you see, as a Quaker, he was an objector. But they all went of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Did you have any women teaching you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. 'Cos apart from the Headmaster, you see, we had to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. I should have asked you this before, it was a mixed school? Boys and Girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 How many standards were there in the school, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I think they went up to standard 6, and there would have\'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And would there have been one class for each or would there have been some of the classes together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Well we were in the top class. People would begin to get sorted out a bit. There would be a few who perhaps could read a book on their own, or something of that sort, which my hav
e been a question of ability but also this lack of teachers, you see, which I can't really say now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Have you any idea how many children there were in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well there would be six classes with about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname metricconverter}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname ProductID}
{\xmlattrvalue 40 in}}}40 in{\*\xmlclose} a class, I suppose, probably more. I'm not sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. There was often large classes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Very many. In the one class you'd get all grades, all round. In some cases the school children would have to go pea picking and come to school and fall asleep they'd been up since three o'clock i
n the morning pea picking. I never suffered from that though. Because we had the little extra me father was able to get. But lots did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. You never went out doing any of that kind of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And what about the others in the family? Did they not do so either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. Did your mother ever do anything like that after she stopped working at the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You don't remember her doing it. Do you think that after she stopped at the mill she stopped working altogether outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 She didn't take in any work, washing or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Do you remember her being any different after she stopped work? Do you have any actual conscious memory of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No, because you see when she stopped work I had only just begun to be conscious of things around me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Yes, so when you remember her being very tired it was when you were much older you think? It was more realising the toll her life had taken of her, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Because w
e rather took everything for granted. We suffered but we didn't think we were 'hard done by' would be the expression, used. I mean, I went to work at the age of, on my 13}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 th}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024  birthday, and working from six o'clock in the morning, 'til about seven o'clock at night, but it didn't seem anything wrong in that to me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Because it's what other people did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, that's how things were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 That first job, what was it exactly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well on a baker's cart, actually. My brother worked for this man as a baker u
ntil he went in the Army. Then on Saturdays I'd go with this man to ride round the countryside, all round Great Tey Chappel and that, in his horse and cart, for the pleasure of it and plus sixpence. And naturally, when they wanted somebody, I was the idea
l fellow to pick on. So I got there at six o'clock in the morning and helped in the bake house make the bread. Eleven o'clock we'd go off in the cart round the countryside to these villages, it was quite a distance really, Great Tey, Oxted, Chappel, Earls
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10486296\charrsid11999024  C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10486296\charrsid11999024 ln}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 e and perhaps home at seven o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And did you have somebody with you while you were out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 A man. Oh yes, see, I was only 13. He drove.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And you got down,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And helped deliver the bread. Sometimes half a mile down a side road 
while he was in a local pub at Great Tey or something, you know. And I can remember even the last call. It could be dark and snowy, perhaps he'd go into a house and sit and have a cup of tea and a chat, and I'd sit outside in this high horse and cart, per
haps pouring with rain, or snowing, but nobody bothered, including myself. You took it for granted. I don't know why, because I've always thought of myself as a rebel, but I can't see how I sat so complacently on there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And no cover?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. Unless yo
u pulled a rag or something over you. You might have two coats and get wet through in a day, but you still kept warm. I do remember this woman coming out and asking if I'd like a piece of bread and jam. It seemed to be a great thing in those days, offerin
g you a bit of bread and jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Were you pleased when she did that, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
No. I wanted to go home. And so did my horse. I've often said that to my wife. She would worry about me, but she wouldn't worry about the horse.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 What was the man like? Was he a pleasant person to be\'85 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 How much bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh sometimes we'd get, you know, half of what we'd call a we sold on the cart, you know. I don't know if you know what a is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I don't I'm afraid. Is it the name of a type of loaf?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. We were not short of bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. So you would not bring the bread with you, you would have the bread from your van?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Sometimes. Probably mostly brought it from home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Made into sandwiches, or sort of separate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Bits of bread and butter and a piece of cheese, you see, and have something off the cart later.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Anything to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No cold tea? You don't remember. And did you have that for your breakfast as well, because presumably you didn't have, or did you 
eat something before you left home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well we'd eat breakfast in the bake house, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I see. They fed you breakfast there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 They didn't, nobody gave you anything in those days. But I could perhaps cook a little piece of bacon in the oven on
 occasion, but it would be mostly bread again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not porridge there, presumably?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. Did you quite often cook yourself a bit of bacon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I don't remember if I did it very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And then bread and cheese for your lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And what else in the day? Nothing else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not until I got home at night and then mother would usually have something cooked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. So the bread and jam, which you used to have for tea, when you started work, would include something cooked as well would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. But it would be, you see, coming home later and missing the midday meal, I would have a cooked meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 She would serve a dinner for you, would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 She wouldn't cook fresh, it would be a dinner saved would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Probably, or she might even cook fresh, but anyway I had a hot dinner when I got home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
You had a hot dinner, yes. Do you remember feeling, sort of, in the day, that, you know, you weren't getting enough to eat? Do you think you suffered at all from bread and cheese and \{BLANK\}
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
No, I don't think we did suffer from that. But, I think, you know, that parents really struggled to feed us well, that was the important thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Now, I realize from what you were telling me, that you had enough when y
ou were at school probably, but I was thinking about this long day out in all weathers with just bread and cheese and nothing hot, whether, you know, you felt any feeling of lack..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You didn't? And did you work on Saturdays as well with the cart?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 All day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 All day. Probably later on Saturdays, 'cos you had to take bread out for the weekends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, I know what I was asking you before we changed tapes. What was the man like? How did you get on with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not particularly
 pleasant character, but I had no one really to compare him with, you see. And he was not unpleasant, but people were not kind in any sentimental way in those days. Everybody was having a hard life and I mean you didn't question these things.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 When yo
u say, 'kind in a sentimental way', do you think that people were, a bit kinder with children, I mean I would think of you almost as a child at thirteen than they would be today? Do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh yes. I don't mean that we didn't get love. But there wa
sn't time for, you know, we were never fussed because nobody had the opportunity or the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. And did he talk to you? Was he companionable at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, he'd talk, but I can't remember just what about, you know. It would be mostly about the work and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You don't remember feeling lonely in the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. I was happy out in the countryside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Even in the winter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Even in the winter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You liked the country-side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And the horse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And you liked the ho
rse. And do you remember if going to work changed your outlook on life at all, or your views about society, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You don't think it changed you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. Did you come into contact with people
 that you hadn't met before, contact of a deep kind, I mean, that you got to know through your work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. Not 'til later on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not 'til later on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I mean this was thirteen years old and getting to deep\'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. And presumably the people you met was just a very brief contact of delivery.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Brief contact, of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And just one man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 What pay did you get there? I think you may have mentioned before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Five shillings, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Five shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Five shillings a week. I had a shilling pocket money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And you gave four shillings to your mother, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Did you have to save towards your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not out of my pocket money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. Would she do that do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And what did you spend your pocket money on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Well, it was on perhaps sweets. I don't think I was smoking, 'cos I wouldn't be smoking at that age. Or there might be a fair. A fair might come into town and you'd go to that. Occasionally a tuppeny gap. (gaff?)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 What is a tuppeny gap? (gaff)?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
There'd be a portable theatre come and put up in one of the meadows in the town, and they would run plays. And they was a repertory company and was changing every night. You see, a trave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10486296\charrsid11999024 l}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 ling repertory comp
any. And, terribly cold, no heating, I remember I've sat in there, tiered up on just wooden planks, and I've felt cramp, you know, almost got like cricket balls underneath my feet. Just sat there and listened. And the people on one occasion they stayed he
re quite a time and got friendly with people. Course they had a hard struggle. Then there would have been, the play would have been, you know, \'93Maria Martin in the Red Barn\'94, \'93East Lynn\'94, and all those things. \'93The Face at the Window\'94.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I've heard of \'93East Lynn\'94 and \'93The Red Barn\'94. What was the first one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10486296\charrsid11999024 "Mar}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 ia Martin", you've never heard of that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No I haven't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well, this was a murder that took place at Polstead. A village. Murdered - this girl was supposed to have been murdered in the R
ed Barn at Polstead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh. It was \'93Maria Martin in the Red Barn\'94 was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Murdered in the Red Barn. This actually did happen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And they made a kind of play out of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. They made this melodrama sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And did they do anything, sort of like "Dick Turpin's Ride to York", or anything like that. Do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I've got a vague recollection of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Was it usually just one play done each night, or were there\'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 One play a night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And how long would they normally stay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Normally a fortnight, but I know on one occasion, I think they got stopped so then, you know, financially, so they couldn't move on, you see. Course it gradually died out, you see, and this probably was the dying years of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And what about the fair? What time of year was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well any time in the summer you might have had a fair come, you know, the trave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10486296\charrsid11999024 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 ling fair. But just out of my reach, but my older sister would remember when there used to be a Halstead Fair. Th
at would be in a meadow about a couple of miles out, down one of the lanes, and they used to go, but I never went. But my older sister can remember this, that would be the Halstead Fair, incidentally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And tell me about the Sunday School you went to the Congregational one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Congregational one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And did you go once or twice a day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Once a day on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Once a day. And would that be in the morning or in the afternoon?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Afternoon. And did you have special Sunday clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You did. And did you go to Church as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. Just to Sunday School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, as we got older we'd go to the Church, to the Congregational Church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. At about what age would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Early teens. And then I went to the Baptist, because they had a sort of a Youth Club, and I went, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And did you stop going to Sunday School when you started going to the Service, or did you continue at both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I don't really remember, you know. It's quite blurred. I couldn't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But when you changed to the Baptist, did you stop going altogether to the Congregational one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I didn't go to the Congregational when used to go to this Baptist, Young Men's Institute, kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. What age were you when you started going there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Probably fifteen or sixteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Tell me about it - what sort of Institute was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well, we just met on a Sunday afternoon and sang a few hymns, you know, \'93Pull for the Shore\'94 and other things, arranging hymns, 
and someone would come and speak. And not always to my liking, even, you know, at that age. Oh we came to some of them, one about Trades Unions or Labour we'd like, you know. You'd get all sorts that got involved to come and speak.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Were you able to argue with them at all, or discuss what they said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well, there was a Mr. Eels, used to run this place and I remember this one particular thing, a man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8855084\charrsid11999024  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 referring to Trades Unions and said something about a pig was in the sty and would always be a pig
, or something of that sort of thing, you know, which got my back up and this Mr. Eels, knowing me, rather brought the thing to a close and I said I think he could see my heckles rising!
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And did you have anything else, I mean, were there any sort of cultural or educational activity attached to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
There wasn't much in the way of education. But we'd have a little camp locally once a year. But the Sunday School treats we used to have. Yes, only then they'd come from the new Congregational. Whi
ch was a great thing in town. The Sunday School treat and once a year, and you'd be taken in a wagon, you know, a farm wagon and a couple of horses in one of these big farm wagons to the venue, the treat. A big tent. And slab cake and tea and that sort of
 
thing. Races. And, if I'm not diverting, there would be the Co-op treat once a year, which was a great event. Then we'd meet down by where the Co-op is now. We'd meet there and if you were lucky you'd grab a big flag and wished you hadn't by the end of th
e
 journey. And we'd march up the street behind the Halstead Town Band up the Halstead High Street and down Parsley Street and into a meadow. Then there'd be this treat. There again there'd be a big marquee and a tea and that, and races and scrambling about
 and all that sort of thing, but a really great day. You know. Nothing really can compare with it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. What sort of flag would it be that you'd grab?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, I expect they were all to do with the co-operative movement, you know. You'd just grab the biggest one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Were they kind of banners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Sort of banners, you know, anything that was a flag, you know, made that you could wave and you felt you were part of it if you'd got a nice big flag, but by the time you'd finished you'd realized that t
hose who hadn't been lucky enough to get a flag were eventually the lucky ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And did adults go along too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh yes. Oh, half the town turned out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, this was the Co-op one, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 A treat for all ages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 A treat for all ages, yes it would be. Quite a big do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 For members of all the Co-op would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And was the Co-op pretty strong in Halstead?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. It was quite strong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And for that Sunday School treat, did any of the mothers go on that too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Yes they would come along and laugh and join in like, not in to the tea of course, that was for the children, except the people who were helping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Do you ever remember going to the seaside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I remember going the first time I went to Dovercourt on a cheap excursion. That was my first trip to the seaside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Any idea how old you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Eleven or twelve perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Was that with your parents, that you went to Dovercourt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. It was a family outing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 A family outing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Was that a day excursion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And do you remember enjoying it? How you felt about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. It was a great day. And another thing that stands out in my mind, was we hired a wagonette, if you know what tha
t is, and took the family through the country lanes, to a place called Henney, Henney Swan, near the river, and we had tea there on the bank, and that was a great day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But there weren't sort of regular family outings, every weekend, or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh no. Our parents probably had to save for this sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And so you enjoyed it all the more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh yes. I mean it stands out in my memory. I mean, I've been to all sorts of places since and nothing really compares with it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Now how long did you keep that job when you were going round with the baker's cart?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 About a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 About a year. And what was the next job that you got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I left there and went down to the local foundry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Was that the same foundry as your father worked at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And what kind of job did you do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Iron moulding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And was it the same sort of work that your father was doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well in principle, but of course elementary to start with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Was it an apprenticeship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Did they have apprentices there at the foundry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
No. You went in and you started work, one of the other lads would just give you a start. You were on piece work from the moment you walked into the place. You just had, you were paid for what you could do, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Was everyone working on piece work basis at that place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not quite all but most of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And certainly all the younger people were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. The lighting was by gas pipes hanging down and spreading out in a T sha
pe with little fan jets and I just marvel now how anyone could see, you know, in the dark, with our present system of lighting, because all the floor, everything, was black. Black sand, you see, which is being burnt, you see, sand. So everything was black
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And the walls were black too were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Well they were white-washed, but then of course they soon got dirty, with the fumes and that kind of thing, so you got very little reflection.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And there were just these gas jets?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Gas jets, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 So it was pretty dim do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Oh very dim I should think, almost dark. Some moulders who were working on close work would have a little tiny, almost like a little aladdin lamp, with a wick in and oil and a little pea like coming out in front, if you understand what I mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. A little what coming out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
A, well a little light. Just a little wick, then into a little bottle almost, of oil, you see, almost sort of a little Aladdin lamp thing, they would just get a little jet of flame coming from this wick, which they could hold close to their work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 To see better, yes? Because the overall light was so inadequate they had to have that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Do you remember being struck by the dimness when you first started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. It's only as I look back comparing it with the present day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Well of course people's homes would have been much darker then of course, too, in the evenings wouldn't they? The lights wouldn't have been so bright with the oil lamps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No but we were one of th
e first people, we had gas quite early as soon as it came out, you know, with a gas mantle. This wasn't too bad a light.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. And you said the hours were six until six, you said, didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I think we left off at half past five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Half past five. But you had to be there at six?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes six o'clock in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 How did they check that you arrived on time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 We had a little brass tally with a number on and you had to hang it on a hook on a board, you see, so they knew who was in and w
ho was out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And would they come and look at that board quite soon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 How much, I mean, how late were you allowed to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 They might've allowed you five minutes before they closed the doors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I see, and when they closed the doors what then if you arrived afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Well you either went home or some people would climb over the wall, course being piece work if they could get in and work. But if you were locked out, this was the expression like, then you had to go home, 
and if you got locked out twice in a week then the second day you were out for the day. A sort of punishment, you see. This could be serious with the men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes of course and if you were, say, frequently late, I mean every week or something like that, did this happen, or was it\'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I don't think that happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. There was too much at stake for people to be late?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And do you remember being late yourself and being locked out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I wasn't particularly terrified, you know, but you were careful not to get late the second time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And then when you put your little brass tally on the board, then you'd start work straight away would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You'd go in and, um, might sit round the fire for a few minutes, you see, and then all get up and start work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, and did you say that at first somebody showed you what to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. I think we were put with another lad on a similar work for a day or two just to get the idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And when would you have your first break?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Lunchtime. Well, when I say lunch-time, dinner time, one 'til two there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 So you worked from six 'til one without a break. No break at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 That's right. No break.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No tea breaks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No tea breaks.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. And were you supervised much? I mean did you have a foreman or people sort of watching you and what you did, and that kind of thing?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not a lot. But you had work to do and you had to get on with it and if you didn't do it well you had no money, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. But you did work in your own time really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. You were comparatively free in a sense that you had your job and you carried on producing as many as you could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. You weren't in any way, if you happened to be particularly slow, would you expect the earnings of any of the other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And then when you came back after your hour, you just started up on the same sort of work again, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I think I made a mistake there. You see, we did go home to breakfast. I think I missed that out, didn't I. I'm sorry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 That's all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 We had Three \endash  quarter hour for breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes and then\'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 From eight o'clock 'til quarter to nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 That would be about the same time as your mother had at the mill wouldn't it, and everyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 So you'd go home to your home them, would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Home for breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 How far away were you from your home to the foundry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Roughly about seven or eight minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And when you got back in the afternoon would you continue in the same kind of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Same kind of work, yes, but then we'd get the metal, what we'd call the metal come, and then we'd melt the metal in the afternoon. Then you'd have to carry this metal and pour it into your moulds, you see, if it makes sense to you. Bu
t in those days we were only thirteen years old and we had to carry these ladles. And you had hand ladles like a T shape here, metal handle, and a ladle, which would hold 28-lbs. of molten metal and we had to walk 70 or {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
metricconverter}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname ProductID}{\xmlattrvalue 80 yards}}}80 yards{\*\xmlclose} and carry this. I mean, now we wouldn't allow a much older lad to do it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Gracious. And two lads carried this ladle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Only one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 One!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You carried it yourself. You went to the furnace and there was a stream of metal coming out and you scooped your ladle under 'til i
t was full of molten metal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 28-lbs of Molten metal for a lad of that age, its an incredible thought, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, I mean, I looked, since I've been foreman and seen youngsters of seventeen and you know, stopped them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. But you were able to do it, you don't remember struggling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well, it was a struggle, but then we did it, obviously.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 What about protective clothing and that kind of thing? Did you have much of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. We had what we called leather spats to prevent the metal co
ming into your shoes, you know, if you spilt it, which in those days often one or other of the lads would be getting burned because of the splashing or spilling of the metal over his feet, you see and getting burned. It doesn't happen so much now because 
of\'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Better safety precautions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well, that was the mere fact of being so young and weak, you know, to do it. You didn't find it easy to control the thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Did these accidents of spilling a bit of metal, did they ever cause blood poisoning
 or anything? Anything like that, that you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
I can't remember, they would sometimes, you'd get this burn and that would tend to grow bigger for a time, you know, it would tend to grow bigger for a time and then to fall off now and again, and then it would gradually heal up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But you don't think that the work itself was hazardous to health as some of that work in the potteries was very hazardous to health.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well the atmosphere wouldn't be pretty congenial. You'd get plenty of dust a
nd then fumes from the molten metal and gases from the moulds. But we didn't think of it in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Do you mean it was really only when you got older and learnt more that you began to realize?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. At the time it wasn't talked about, you mean.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. Just taken for granted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And how did you find the other people you were at work with as workmates? Did you get on all right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. We got on all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 In fact that was, I suppose, a sort o
f pleasure of life, was between yourself and your mates. That was all you had almost to live for, you know, the fun that you could make. We had to make fun of almost everything, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. So it was the sort of companionship side of the work that made it sort of bearable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Yes, and life itself, it was the companionship between your pals of your own age, it seemed to be about the only real thing that kept you going, you know, but we did have fun, we were never bored.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. What sort of fun? In conversation and joking and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And up to mischief even at work, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Was that tolerated, because you were young, by the older people at the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Unless, and until you did something which often you did o
f course to torment the older men, then you had to rely on your legs, or you got a real clout. But you usually managed to escape, you know, and that was all. Taken in good fun.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 How do you think you compared, you thirteen years olds, with the young lads that go and leave school now and go into that kind of work?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well of course you wouldn't get them go at that age now, would you? Actually I was fifteen then you see. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But would you get them at fifteen years olds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes you would get them perhaps a lad of fifteen, but actually its dying out because people are not coming in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Are they not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. This foundry now, had probably only a third of the people working there now, as used to be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Why is that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well its not the sort of job that would attract young people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Its not because there's not the demand for the tortoise, what are they called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 The tortoise stove. But actually they make all sorts of castings, for machine tools. It could be anything. You see, the contra
ct. They make from usually a wooden pattern, or a metal pattern, any shape they want the casting, and you make the mould to this pattern. Then when you lift in the pattern you are left with a cavity the shape of the casting which you wanted to produce. Yo
u
 see. You make internal shapes too which would be done by a core of sand which had been baked in the oven. You fit it all up, you see, then you pour the metal in, and then in the morning when its cooled down you've got a casting in the shape of the patter
n that you used.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And there's still the demand for the casting\'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh good gracious, I mean, needless we couldn't keep on without castings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. I'm wondering why here in Halstead, you say, that people, they don't have the people now, its bec
ause the people don't want the work, not that the industry itself is dying.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. No. But in those days did you consider the work particularly hard, compared with what other lads were doing your age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No not really. Occasionally you migh
t envy someone. A lady in a shop, but, really you didn't envy them because they almost seemed a different breed, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You just didn't compare them? Just like I wouldn't compare myself with the film stars or something? You mean it was a different world?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I don't think usually we would have changed it and stood behind a counter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 That seemed to be the only two comparisons I could make really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 What about working in the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Courtaulds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, there were so few\'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, of course, lots of lads did go to the mill, but I never came across them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But it wasn't in question in your case to go to the mill? It wasn't thought about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. And did your father kind of get the job for you at the Iron Foundry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And can you tell me what your pay was when you started there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I should think probably about 7/6d. then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. It was a jump up from what you had been getting as a baker's boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And did you still give most of it to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And can you remember what you kept back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, probably still a shilling.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 So she did benefit a bit from you getting that better job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And did you get any holiday with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not with pay, No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. Could you take some days off without pay if you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Well you could stay home if you liked and there's one thing that's always peculiar, I think, to this foundry, they spent their Christmas holiday, Christmas Day and Boxing Day
, and the following day the me walk down to the gates outside where the Co-op is now, six o'clock in the morning, tend to accumulate on a cold day, and then someone would say, you know, one of the men, "Well I think we ought to toss up to see whether we'l
l go in or not." And they used to toss a brick up. If it came down we went home, if it stayed up we went in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 How? I see. I was going to ask you how it could possibly stay up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 That would happen on occasion and sometimes we'd actually drift in and t
hen us lads would go and prompt one of the old men, 'cos we could never lead of course, and say, well everybody had a nickname, "Don't you think that's too cold to have to work", you know, 'til he'd put his coat on. Then we'd rush off to another old boy, 
who was called 'silver' "Silver, Daydo's gone home, he said it's too cold to work", until we'd got the whole lot walking out, or until the few left was uneconomical and we'd all be sent home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Yes, so in that sort of way you exerted quite a bit of authority
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Yes. But I think that was peculiar to this foundry. It always seemed silly anyway to get down there at six o'clock in the morning knowing that they wouldn't go in, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. How big was it actually? What was the number of people employed there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 80 or 90 of us, could have been 100, 'cos there were machine shops, too, and pattern shops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And did you when you were there, belong to a Trade Union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. Was it organized then at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. They began to organize later.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. About what age were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 It probably started when the men came back from the war, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 'Cos you went there towards the end of the war, didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. I started there about 1917, or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 About 1917? Yes that's what I worked out. Yes and it wasn't until a little after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Then a few years after that, it would have been before this last war, then I played quite a part in organising everybody into the A.E.U. We did get pretty well 100%. And I 
was Shops Stewards Convener all through the war. 'Til after the war I was made foreman and, you know, had to give that up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. You had to give that up, you mean you retired?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well from this Shop Steward business. I couldn't be foreman and Shop Steward.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. But what about your father? I mean, was he in a Trade Union at all? He couldn't have been there, I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 He would have been in a Moulders Union when it once had started I'm pretty sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And did you take part in any politi
cal activity? During this period up to 1918? You mentioned cleaning out the, I think it was, I.L.P. offices?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Yes. The I.L.P. little club room, that was at twelve years old. I used to come from school and do that. And we were always active if there was
 anything to be active about, you know, as regards the Labour party, and that sort of thing. You see my father was on the local council, board of guardians, co-op committee. He was secretary of the Working Men's Club for over 50 years, for which he had a 
little money for, incidentally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 He did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Then County Council for a spell. So politically within our family there was always a certain political activity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Though you wouldn't at that time, of course, been; I don't know what age they h
ad members for membership of the I.R.P. Were you actually a member at any stage?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well, I wouldn't have been a member. By the virtue of your parents you see, the children used to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Do you remember ever, for example, distributing leaflets or anything, and canvassing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Ooh. I have done, yes. And, of course, jumping this 1918 business, but in the 1924 election I had three weeks off from work with another pal and we run the committee rooms, you see. Yes. But that was past 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But do you r
emember working in any election, you know, within the period? 1906 would be no good because you were too young, and when was the next one? Do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I'm afraid I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 There weren't many I know over that period.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You see there wouldn't have been a labour party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. And were there any kind of clubs or anything of that kind? Organised at the foundry for the young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not at the foundry, no. Did later on. We had a sports club, but that was much later on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But at that time there was nothing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Just one question. I know what the answer will be. Did you feel that workers had different interest from employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Good gracious, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Obviously, 'cos you realised that this, well before you could probably rememb
er realising this, you had sort of absorbed this sort of knowledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh yes. Well the atmosphere at home was bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 The class struggle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 The daily harrows. When I was quite young I remember reading all the parliamentary speeches, you know. If th
ere was anything, you know, a labour man said in the house, then I'd be interested to read it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Do you remember discussing these sort of things with your, you know, people at work at all? Your work fellows?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well I probably discussed it right up 'til the day I left, without much success sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Did you try and convert people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You did, yes. I know you obviously would have done when you got older and got more organized, but I wondered earlier.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well I wouldn't like to say, not when I was around fourteen years old, I shouldn't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You didn't then? I just wondered whether at that time young boys were discussing politics at that particular place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. What sort of things did you do then in the ev
enings at that time? Was it mostly things to do with your father's sort of political activity? There was a Baptist Institute I think you mentioned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes we used to go to the Baptist Men's Institute we used to go to and they had a little club room. In t
he summer this man who sort of organised it, his garden man down to the river, and we used to go swimming in the river. Or we had a week's camping at Downs Hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. That must have been nice. Did you enjoy that, the camping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And swimming in the lake there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Could you swim?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Yes. In fact we walked round the gardens yesterday at Downs Hall and we saw this lake. Incidentally, I won two prizes of a guinea there. I couldn't remember. It was a sort of fete we used to do a swim with umbrell
as up and all sorts of things to entertain, I think it must have been the matron of the Women's Institute or something. They had a fete there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And do you remember who actually taught you to swim or did you just pick it up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I'm not sure at what age this would be, but as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10044904\charrsid11999024 
youths we used to walk to Gosfie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10044904\charrsid11999024 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
 Lake on a Sunday evening through the fields and two of my pals they went in and swam across the lake and suddenly that's when I first became conscious of water. They came out and said it was e
asy, so I said well I'd swim across the lake by August, and I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. What month was that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well that must have been May or something I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And you did by August?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10044904\charrsid11999024 By August I swam across Gosfield}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024  lake and back. From then on 
it was a ritual. Sunday e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10044904\charrsid11999024 venings we all walked to Gosfield}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
 lake, swam across the lake and back. Then walked right all round the outside of the lake, then round, you know, that was altogether about seven or eight miles plus this swim. That was on a Sunday evening. But probably it was 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. In your late teens, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And was it always just boys together. Did the boys tend to keep sort of in a crowd together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 It was boys together, you know, three or four of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And did you have a few particular friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 These ones that you were usually with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I just wondered where you met, where your particular friends, you know, where you got to know them at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well it would be at work or at this Baptist Club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Did you think at that time in Halstead you knew, you know to say hallo to, a large number of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Quite a lot. Everybody seemed to know everybody else. All the families were, I think I've mentioned before
, there were family nicknames, and
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, I remember you telling me that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 In conversation I didn't know whether I would have mentioned these nicknames. But a conversation we might have: she was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10044904\charrsid11999024 Tedd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 y Wig and she married a Dripping Brag, you see, 
and they lived next door to the Snotty Constables, you see, I mean that would be the sort of conversation that they would have. They would link things together.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And when people would say that everybody would know who they meant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, better than any other or any other name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Yes. Do you think it was used to differentiate the different families who had the same name? Or did it happen also with families who had no other\'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 It would seem almost as every family had a family nickname.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Irrespective of if they were big families with lots of branches or not, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. Its the way we used to know people you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. What were the Spurgeons called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Broker Spurgeons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Broker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I don't know why it was, unless it was because my father used to do all this selling, you know, things like pianos, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, I remember, yes that's perhaps where it came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Possibly, although it could have gone back further than that, you know, I'm not sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. But you don't remember a time when they weren't known as that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Do these still exist today, in Halstead today, these nicknames of all the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 They're not in use now. Not family names like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 The older people mostly refer to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But younger people wouldn't use them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I wanted to ask you whether your parents were interested in your progress at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh yes, I think so. We used to have what we called a record or progress card that we used to br
ing home. And, oh, I mean they would be interested in education. And I think the war coming along rather upset everything. And as I look back had I kept on after 1914 I'd probably have gone to Grammar School and could have transferred later on. Not like y
ou people with your universities, mind you it wasn't easy in those days, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh no. Certainly it wasn't. And were there any lessons at school that you particularly disliked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I suppose everybody disliked arithmetic as far as I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And you did too? You disliked it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
And were there any lessons that you particularly liked? You mentioned the excellent head teacher you had, he would read Shakespeare and things like that to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes well that was always more of
 a treat than a lesson. He did this largely because, as I say, there was the teachers gone and there was an overflow of children and he'd take little groups out and read in the playground in the summer time, which was quite a pleasure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 So that wasn't really a lesson?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Can you remember anything else that you particularly liked about being at school? Not necessarily academic things but, you know, outside social activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Can't remember anything exceptional, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. Do you think y
our school days weren't a very important part of your general life, you know, either then or later, you know? Some people look back on their school days and think they were so terribly important, do you think perhaps yours weren't very important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, 
I think its important, I mean, because I believe in education, as I said before, I've been a member of the W.E.A. ever since I realised what I've missed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No, but that's different from saying that - I mean from your particular schooling.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I think 
really most children went because they had to go. And incidentally if some child didn't want to go he was dragged to school. Which intrigues me today, because there are children I can think of a lot now, quite intelligent children, who just opt out of sch
o
ols, I mean in certain problem cases that we know of at hand, and I often wonder whether in our days if they had been dragged to school what would have been the result, would they had been dragged to school what would have been the result, would they have
 conformed. Because I wonder sometimes whether these would hold down a job or anything. We tend to call them schizophrenic. I don't think that would be an exaggeration, but\'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But when they were dragged to school, you mean they were literally dragged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Literally. Screaming to school on occasion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And was the discipline in the school very strict?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Yes. Although I can remember one class which would be the beginning of the war. A young fellow came, he must have been a student teacher and obv
iously wasn't strong enough character. The lads got on to him and they literally did used to fight him on occasions. I've seen them get him across the table, and he'd always keep getting his cane out and hit back. It was all fun and games, you know. "Don'
t let him hit you, skinny!" You see everybody had a nickname then, or smalley, that sort of thing. But it only happened to this one particular fellow and the awkward ones would then rush up with this Edward Baker and usually slap back sort of thing.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Edward Baker was the Headmaster?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 He wasn't the headmaster, he was the Second Master, and a really first class man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. So you had two first class teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. And I knew this Mr. Baker right through 'til a few years ago. 'Cos we had an adul
t school in our department of the W.E.A., which met on Sundays, and he was one of the leaders in that. There was about a dozen to eighteen of us used to go Sundays, you know, to talk about different subjects each week. There was a national adult school an
d we used to issue a handbook with a subject each week and it was all very interesting and discussions. We'd sing hymns, but there'd be people of all denominations and no denominations it didn't matter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 That reminds me, actually, I think you said you went to a Board School am I right? And your sisters went to a Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 When you say Board School, I went to a Council School, what you'd call a Council School.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You call it a Council School? In London they used to call it a Board School? Yes, and your sisters went to a denominational School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 They went across, yes, to St. Andrews School, where they used to opt.. out of religion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, I remember you telling me about that. Why did you go to a different school from them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I think at that time they lived the other end of the town, which was near St. Andrews.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh I see, yes. That was an earlier time? Then they moved house, did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And can you remember any activities at the school like sort of Speech Days, and O
pen Days, and that sort of thing? I know they were rare at most school at that time, but I wondered if your school had them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well this would be about Christmas. This headmaster of ours, this Mr. Matthews, he'd get us all sitting in the Hall on the flo
or and he'd tell a story and he'd also illustrate the people in the story. He'd have a pencil or whatever it was in each hand and he'd have sheets of paper on the blackboard and easel and he'd say "Oh, this is Mr. Steamley", you see, and he could draw lik
e this, you see, he got this Mr. Steamley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Like a cartoon strip as it were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Yes, he'd draw perfectly with the two hands like that. And he'd give lectures at the W.E.A. and that, you know. Pickwick Papers, and he'd draw Sam Weller, you know, and ev
entually made us all clap and laugh. He really was a wonderful man. A real old Mr. Chips, you know, and such a kind face, you know, and a white moustache. We were lucky.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I bet you enjoyed that didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh yes, the children loved it. Then perha
ps we had a little speech or something at the end, which I think it was a last minute shopping affair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 To get money in the end?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. There weren't school funds then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And he had a piece of ground behind his house and he let u
s play cricket on that in twos. And when the playground was enlarged when they had this new school built it included, incorporated, an orchard, and he always gave some of these apples and pears, and gave to the boys. And if there was anything that I liked
 about the schooldays it was this Mr. Matthews.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Mr. Edward Baker certainly had a great influence on my life. The twice one are two, I'm not so sure just what effect that had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well from what you tell me it sounds as if your real educatio
n has been what you have done for yourself later, in going to classes and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But I'm sure that these two people had an influence..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Their influence, oh yes, to get you interested.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 They didn't have the opportunity to teach\'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But they 
made you realise that there was something in education whereas a lot of people go to school and come out more unwilling than they would have been if they'd never gone, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well I've been an active, I mean I'm on the district council now for W.E.A
. Cambridge. Been one for years, you know, for district council. Incidentally, I don't know if its anything to do with this\'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 This old builder, local builder, you see, he'd built this cinema on contract, then they hadn't enough money to pay him or some
thing, so they made him manager of this cinema. And he had a little beard and he looked just like one of these Keystone Policemen - if you've ever seen a Keystone Film. And he ran this cinema and we used to go in and one of the tricks was, there was a sor
t
 of concrete floor, take a bar of iron in and lay down at the back and roll it down to the front with a clatter - these were silent films of course - then we'd hand it back and roll it down again. And going in sometimes, say, "Box of matches, Tom. We've c
o
me in for a box of matches." "Oh yes, you can come in". And we'd give him a box of matches to go in, 'cos we'd collected dead matches anyway, so we'd get in for a box of matches. Or one would go in with a ticket and then he'd make a point of saying to Tom
,
 as he came out "Tom, just want to slip out to the shop", and he'd give a mate this half-ticket, you see he could go back because he'd made a point of being noticed going in and then someone else would go in with his ticket, you see. And the whole place w
a
s run by youngsters, you see. There was almost an underground movement within the cinema. So that ran from an old gas engine, and they could turn the gas off and the engine would stop, you see, and then the film would gradually fade from the screen. And m
o
st of us would sing a song "These pictures are no good, are no good, are no good; These pictures are no good, they fade away." And this old fella, Tom, would rush down the aisle to the engine, and he hadn't a clue about it, you see, so they used to really
 
run this for him in this way, but we had tremendous fun, apart from the pictures. And if there was a good picture on at another place, or if there was a fair or a circus come into a town, and these lads who operated the metal thing wanted to go. They'd co
l
lect the films from the station, take 'em up on the roof and hide 'em, and say the film hadn't come, you see. And then he'd get all the people in, you see. Then they'd tell him "Well Tom, you'll have to tell them something, you can't just leave them there
. You'll have to go and make an announcement." "Well what am I going to say?" "Well tell 'em the bloody films 'ent come." And he would go on and he'd say "Sorry ladies and gentlemen, we can't show tonight, the bloody films 'ent come."
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 What did the ladies and gentlemen do to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
There never were any ladies and gentlemen. Then assure everybody you could have your ticket or your money. So we'd stand in the aisle which was a queer thing, and as you went out you either got a ticket or your money back
. So you'd get a ticket and then come round the back and join in the queue and, at the back, and then perhaps come round and take your money, and this would go on. And the next night someone would ask Tom, \'93How you getting on Tom?\'94 \'93
Full House and 'ent took a bloody halfpenny.\'94 So what with giving all these tickets and money away, when they'd come down from the gallery he hadn't got any money to give 'em. You see we used to have great fun, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You really had him tied up!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And the lads in the o
perating box, they made a slide you see of a picture of Tom Biggs with his little beard and that, and a trowel, as a brick layer, you see, and the thing was this. They'd slip this slide in when Tom wasn't looking and then when this come on "Tom Biggs" fro
m
 the whole audience, then poor old Tom would come rushing in and say "What is it, what's going on here?" You know, and sometimes they'd put a cord across the aisle then stop the engine and as Tom rushed down to investigate what's happened at the engine, h
e
'd trip over this rope, you see, in the aisle, sprawling, and he'd swear. I wont repeat what he'd said, but real venomous language. I'm afraid I shall get carried away if I keep on with this, but that's how we'd made our fun, you see. Well I'd better leav
e
 you with Mr. Watts, because I'm sure we shall go on indefinitely. Some sort of guilt complex regards sex and I was never happy with the opposite sex. Although I could talk to W.E.A. ladies, easily, but put me in a room with a factory girl and I was absol
utely tongue-tied for some reason or other. And eventually I met my wife at the W.E.A. Anyway, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13508643\charrsid11999024 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
hese friends suddenly turned up on Sunday night, and instead of a rough and ready clothes to go with lake, in navy blue suits and bowler hats. That silly young woman - the same young woman became \{ILLEGIBLE\}
, as a matter of fact the one who one lost, if you understand what I mean.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You mean, he lost her in the end?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well, he made a mistake in the one they were fighting for. The one who won the battle lost
 the fight, sort of thing, because it wasn't good for him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You mean he married her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 He married her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And it wasn't a success?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. But anyway, this left me very... sort of melancholy and I was completely on me own, and Sunday evenings I s
tarted walking all round Marks Hall and Appleby, into the woods and round. I did this for quite a time, all alone. In a sense I was happy and I became almost part of nature, if you know what I mean, near all the animals and birds and felt and felt like so
m
ething akin with them. It's so difficult to explain. But although I was a bit melancholy at the time, if that's the right word, I felt... you know, my life had changed and I was at a loss because I couldn't follow these other people in their pursuits. So 
f
or quite a long time I did this walking on my own, into the woods and fields. Miles, entirely alone. Which did something good for me, I'm sure, because I've always loved the countryside, and my wife does, and that is one of our greatest pleasures. But tha
t's enough said I'm quite sure. I'll start with your question.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
No, that's very interesting. But the interesting thing, too, was that you said you were shy with these girls, do you think it was because you found them difficult to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I could never use the same sort of small backchat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Because you were so serious?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Yes. It would... well, it must have been a guilt complex with regard to sex, somehow or other. Well, I was always perfectly all right talking, as I say, with these W.E.A. peop
le because they had something in common and this other business didn't come into it, you see, it wasn't a sex relationship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But perhaps it wasn't just guilt. Perhaps it was that you liked, in all your relationships with people, to have things to talk 
about, whether they were\'85 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
I just couldn't run a conversation on the silly little backchat that I've heard these other people do, you know. I was frightened off. The locals would go to White Colne, or something, Sunday evening and talk with a group o
f girls, just silly talk and... well, vulgar, almost, not that I claim to be much different, but I just could not join that, or stand in shop doors and trip girls up as they come by, I just couldn't possibly. And I got... even frightened me further away f
rom it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Was it a long time before you got over this worry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Oh, quite a long time, until eventually I managed to stop and invite my wife out for a walk after a W.E.A. meeting and that was one of the best things that has happened. See, I owe my life
 to the W.E.A., so you must forgive us if we seem to be talking about it all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I can understand this, and particularly if you met your wife that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And we both have common interests, and walking. As I say, we belong to the Colchester Ra
mblers now. Although we've got a car walking is our sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Can you just tell me, when these Sunday walks with your group of friends ended, about how old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I suppose about 17, perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And when you stopped going for the w
alks with them did anyone sort of remark on this? I mean, did your mother and father kind of take an interest in your friendships and your social life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I think they wondered. Right up to the last my mother wondered what had happened. She didn't live t
o see me get married to Rose, but I'm sure that she would have been thrilled to bits. At one time, I remember on one occasion her saying, 'I wish you'd get a girlfriend' - or whatever term she used. And I think she was feeling she was on the way out and w
hat would happen to Reg, you know, because I was different to the others, with... well, Shakespeare and that sort of thing. I'm not setting meself up as a scholar, but... 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I know what you mean, you had these interests.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 What was your relationship with your sisters like? I forget how many other brothers. It was mostly girls, wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. Two brothers older, except one died, and one younger. The youngest one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Was Beverley a boy, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Beverley was a boy.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I was wondering, you kn
ow, with your particular interests, a serious studious bent that you had how you got on with your sisters and brothers? Were there any others like you in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No, not quite like me, I was on my own in lots of ways. I don't mean they were illite
rate or anything of that kind, of course, but I think probably the fact that I didn't have these relationships with the opposite sex, you see, I had to do something, although I was obviously interested. I'd taken Shakespear down off the shelf lots of time
s
 before I ever got interested. And I went to the cinema once, there was a picture with... like a clover in the day, 'King Lear', just a little snippet. Oh, and I did want to know what happened. I went home and got out King Lear and sat up, and then I real
i
sed the beauty of the language and, you know... That was Shakespeare, or at least, to me. Then I waded through, not the historical plays so much, but... probably got this complex and thought romance was Romeo and Juliet, you know. May have got the whole t
hing twisted up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 With your sisters and brothers you had... ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 We had a good relationship, but not quite... 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not deep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Do you remember confiding in them and talking to them about the things you felt, about the woods and the animals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Oh, no. No, I don't remember talking about it. But they all enjoyed the countryside because everybody walked in... you had to walk. You walked to Gosfield or Hedingham, or anywhere, where there was a garden par Four miles there and back was unimpor
tant. You went and paid your threepence into the garden party, or at least they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 What were these garden parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, well, if you can imagine, somebody would open the gardens and it would be a party. Sometimes, perhaps, a band, and they might
 dance, and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And you paid something to do in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 A penny, or 3d., probably, to go in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 A lot of people used to do, did they, the working people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. My sisters would, in any case, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Were you not, perhaps, a bit closer to one of the family than any of the others, or did you feel the same, really, about all of them?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Roughly the same about all of them, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 We were never an emotional family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You weren't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You didn't express emotion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
No kissing or anything of that sort within the family. And even my brother going off to War, we'd shake hands and say 'good-bye'. And when he came home on leave, or whatever, you just accepted them, he was back and away you went, but no fa
lling on each other's necks, or anything of that sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 What about tears, and that kind of thing, do you remember crying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not even your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not even my mother, no, I don't ever think her shed a tear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Can you remember if your mother and father were strict about your general behaviour? Manners, and standards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Within reason, yes, but of course, with a big family, manners was not like what we'd expect today, perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Can you remember any of the type of things in general behaviour or manners that they thought important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well, Mother didn't like me to mix with people who she thought }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9330349\charrsid11999024 
were... I don't mean poor, but h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 ooligan type, you know. She would say, 'I wouldn't go out with so-and-so', you know, 'he's not too good'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Would that be the phrase she used? It's interesting to know the kind of ways people put things at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No, well, she 'might say, 'I don't like him'. Mind, you, I still did, but... I don't think she understood, but that was... we were all a
s bad as my mother, I think, you know, quick answers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But she saw difference, did she, in the working classes she saw big differences in standards, herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well, she might have thought, oh, this fellow'll lead him into stealing apples. You know,
 or something of that sort, never anything terrible, but she just wanted her children anyway to conform to a certain standard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You are referring here to particular children she didn't like you to run around with, do you know if she had any feelings of
 being different from other women in her same kind of walk of life, that she didn't like the way they lived, and this sort of thing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Can you remember whether she cared about table manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, within certain limits, yes, but not to the point of being fastidious or anything of that sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 What things did she consider you should do? And not do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well, I can't really remember anything particular, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 One or two things were common at that time. Quite a lot of families weren't allowed to talk at all at meals, were you allowed to talk?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, we were allowed to talk, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Were you allowed to leave food on your plates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 We were allowed to, but it was a very rare thing. The food was put on your 
plate and you felt that you were obliged to eat it, although it was never any hardship, but you just automatically cleared your plate up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Were you allowed to pick and choose what you would have on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, it was put on your place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Some of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Did you all have to wait until everyone had finished before you got down from the table when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You could get off your chair when you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, if you'd finished you could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Did you all sit down together for meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, usually, because we'd all gone on from \{ILLEGIBLE\}
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I remember now, I asked you that last week. I don't think I asked you whether your father was served first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I don't remember, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You say you think he probably would have been served first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Do you think he would have had the same food? He wouldn't have had a bit extra, better food?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 He might have had a bit extra \{ILLEGIBLE\}
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But the same food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 The same food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Do you know if your mother stinted herself at all with food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 My guess is that she would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Because she was that kind of person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But you don't know for a fact?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I don't know for a fact. She would have served everyone else first, I'm pretty sure of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And had what was left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
You were telling me about her certain standards, you know, that she wouldn't like you to mix just anybody, do you remember if she punished you if you did do anything wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You weren't punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not in any kind of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No, I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Do you ever remember being threatened with a punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not really, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 That's pretty unusual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I can only remember my brother, once, he was p
unished by my father for stealing apples from a house down the road. I think that's the only occasion I can remember my father - I don't know about losing his temper. I've never known him to lose his temper or get out of his equilibrium in any shape or fr
om. Always on the same key.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But he did so on that occasion?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 On that occasion I do remember my brother, you know, getting what we call a good hiding, for this... stealing apples from a house nearby.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 What would he have used?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I don't know 
whether he used a stick or not, I didn't witness it, you know, but I just remember an incident of that sort. That's the only incident that I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Did you have any pocket money at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 A shilling on occasions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I meant actually, were 
you ever given anything like a halfpenny, or a farthing, before you started earning a little? Do you ever remember having been given a little money to spend yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 We might have been given a halfpenny for just a little sherbert dab, or some such thing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But it wasn't a regular thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Did you have birthday parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Or Christmas parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Christmas, yes. Christmas was a real... that was the day of the year, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 What was it like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Well, there was the Sta. Claus at Christmas, of course, when we were young looking for things in our stockings, a small prize, you know. And then come down, you know, and in the house there'd be fruit and that sort of thing and a fire, of cour
se, in the front room. Then there'd be a more elaborate dinner, that sort of thing. Then we'd come home to tea. Then in the evening the men would go out, perhaps to a public house, come back and we'd have supper which would usually be... the usual thing u
s
ed to be a rabbit pie; make one or perhaps two rabbit pies, on the size of the group that was gathered, you know, the family come along. And have this rabbit pie for supper, usually. And then to sort of wind the evening up we used to have... I'm not sure 
w
hether they were prunes or something like that on a plate poured over with brandy - we used to call them snap dragons - turn the light out and set light to the brandy and everybody would pick up these flaming... prunes, I think they must have been. It use
d to be, you know, sort of part of the ritual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And after that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well, they'd be sitting talking and children playing with their toys until we went to bed, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 There were always Christmas presents, were there, for everybody in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
For the children. I can just remember on one occasion, my elder brother, he was getting older, you see and he felt in his stocking and, oh, he'd got something and he thought he'd got a coconut. It turned out to be a turnip. He'd finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You mean that was the bottom of the... the end?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 It was the end. He was getting too old for it. I suppose, you see, that was his way old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 What sort of age would he have been then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Don't know. 16 perhaps, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Sixteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well, it's a job to say. That's purely a guess.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 He was quite old? I mean, the stocking went on for quite a long time, did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes. No, he couldn't have been 16, I'm sorry. I just don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Did you have a Christmas tree?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 On occasions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Do you remember ever going Carol singing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I think I have on one or two occasions. But not this going and knocking on the door and, you know, cadging like the children do now.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You didn't do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Would your parents have disapproved of that sort of thing, do you thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, I'm sure they would, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You didn't collect pennies for Guy Fawkes and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No, I didn't, but that was done. I don't remember actually doing it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I wonder if you had any awareness of how
 people thought about you, if you ever came into contact with people with sort of snobbish attitudes, or suffered in this way at all as a child? Or young lad?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I can't remember any particular instances, but looking back I feel sure that we were consid
ered a different breed, you know. I feel pretty certain of that, you know. It's a complete change now. We were regarded as something different, in the way that I think that your people look on the blacks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But do you think in this society you yourself moved in were you all the same class, or did you come into contact with middle-class people?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
No, we didn't. Not the children, anyway. Father might have done. I always remember the first time he went to the County Council and he came home and said, lik
e, they were nearly all farmers and such like. And someone said, 'and how much ground do you own, Mr. Spurgeon?' And he said, 'well, about what you'd get in a flower pot'. And, you see, that was the criterion, and they never had anyone like him there befo
re. My first trip to London, switch this off if it's irrelevant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Is it out of the period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 It probably was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well, let's have it anyway if it's about this sort of thing. It's very interesting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 He had to go to a meeting at \{ILLEGIBLE\}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9201054\charrsid11999024  Place House}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
, they used to have the County Council meetings there, and I went to London with him and sat in Finsbury Circus Gardens 'till he came out. I was scared to move out of... my first trip to London. But it would have been after '18.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, I thin
k you said it was somewhere in the 1920s he got on the Council, wasn't it? But obviously, as you were brought up with these progressive views, you would have been brought up not to consider that some people were your betters, as the majority of working cl
ass children were brought up to believe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 We were brought up to consider that, but it was difficult always to just eradicate it from your nature \{BLANK\} I think, anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You mean you were brought up to consider that you were Legally, we were as goo
d as anyone else, but in actual fact that took a long time to really work it into your system, you know, because... 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Because of the whole way society was organised, do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Do you feel your father had a feeling himself, though, of his... of consciousness of his own equality as a man with other men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, I think so.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You think he'd sort of absorbed this idea fully?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I should think so, as much as anyone did in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I wondered if you ever remember seeing him wi
th people with, say, more money or with higher status, how his bearing was with them. Was he quite confident, do you think, in his bearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 He would have been, but at that age I wouldn't have been in... 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You wouldn't have seen these interactions, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. But I mean, obviously, seeing as he... going on to the Councy Council, they'd all be different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 If he wasn't a man of confidence he'd never have gone in for that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And what about your mother, was she deferential, or would she stand up for herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Oh, she'd stand up for herself. But of course, you didn't contact these people, you see, you didn't get mixed up with the Church and with the Establishment. You didn't make the contacts, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Your parents didn't; they weren't Church people at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No. Although they allowed us to go to Sunday School and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And do you think that despite your parent's views, they weren't cold-shouldered at all by people, despite their views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You mean... ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 In a neighbourly... 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 This made no difference to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No, well, you see, they'd probably be looked up to, in a sense, and be applied to for help in some ways, if you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Because they were better educated?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, I've heard people say 'ask Mr. Spurgeon what to do', you know, if they had any complications.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Did people often come to the house to see your father about things?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I think they must have done, but I haven't any particular recollections about it at that stage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Do you remember any entertaining in the home? Entertaining to Sunday tea or anything of that kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 It'd be mostly the family, members of the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You mean your own particular family, or other relatives, too? Like your grandmother and this sort of thing. Would they come in for meals?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
No, very rarely my grandmother. Well, the little grannie who used to live up here probably would walk into town and she would've had a meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 From Whiteash Green, that one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Whitessh Green, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But you wouldn't have people in on a Sunday to tea and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Not strangers, to my knowledge. When I say 'strangers', you know... 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Non-family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Non-family, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Is there more of that today, do you think, of having people in to meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Oh, yes. People can afford to entertain, now, can't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Do you remember being brought up to have any attitudes towards the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 None at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Some children are brought up to sort of fear the police.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Oh, well, you'd tend to get threatened, you know, 'I'll tell the policeman', or something like that, and... well, you did feel that something terrible could happen if the police were informed about this, that o
r the other. They were used as a threat. I think that was pretty general. The children coming from the workhouse'd be dressed in corduroy suits and tremendously heavy shoes. Boots. Then there'd be another little old man in the same sort of attire, come an
d
 meet them out of school. They were usually, you know, not particularly intelligent, you know, to be... when I say 'low' don't misunderstand me. I wouldn't want to be misunderstood classwise, you know. But they used to come to school and were very conspic
u
ous by their dress. And speaking about these shoes, there used to be some organization whether it was a local charity or not, whereby if you were very poor you could get a pair of boots. But they were terrific. They wouldn't... they'd come up to about her
e
, and they could've almost been made, you know, with metal for all the bend you could get, and I mean, children used to go along in them - we never suffered from it, well, I mean, we wouldn't have had that sort of charity, anyway - but they walked almost 
like \{BLANK\}
, if you know what I mean. These terrific things. And it's a wonder their feet weren't crippled for life. Hob-nailed boots. The thing was that they'd got to last forever. And the uppers were so stiff, they never bent. It wouldn't bend at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And that was the type these workhouse children wore, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Well, yes. And there was a charity, whether that was from local, or the authorities, or what, but you could apply and... well, you'd have to answer all sorts of questions, I suppose, and you could get these boots. But we never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 And these children who came from the workhouse, they weren't boarded out in Halstead, they then returned to the Union, did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 They returned to the Union, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Do you remember whether they were cold-shouldered by the other children? I know this happened in Gt. Bentley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
No, I don't think so. They were obviously conspicuous by their dress and they were a little different. I mean, they were extremely poor and conscious of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Were they a bit cowed, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I should think so. Well, they would be, wouldn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But you don't remember them being taunted or in any way discriminated against?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Do you remember, in the school generally, were children treated much the same, by the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, I think so. As far as I can recall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You were more on a level at your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I think so. Well, there were some who were quite badly dressed, you know, and I can think of one woman who - you know, it 
shocks me now when I think of her. Now she's got a home and his houseproud and really gone the other extreme, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You mean you remember how badly she was dressed when she was sent to school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Yes, and
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But you weren't much aware of class differences and this sort of thing at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Were there private schools in the town, that you were aware of the children there being different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No, I don't remember any private schools. There was a grammar school, of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Mr. Wash was saying that it was suggested that he sit for the entrance to the grammar school, was this ever an idea in your case?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well, I wondered what happened in my case, but I can only think I missed that by virtue of leaving at 13m and ... because I r
emember some of my contemporaries going to the grammar school. But I never went in for this exam, 'cos I feel sure I should have gone, because I was always second in the class. There was one chap always one step ahead of me. So I feel sure that, you know,
 had \{ILLEGIBLE\}
, that I should have passed to go to the grammar school, and if my parents... I think if they could possibly could, would've allowed me. But I think this leaving school a year beforehand, during the war, and I think I must have missed that, you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Do you remember whether you all had a bath time on a particular day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Yes, we would be bathed once a week, probably on a Friday night, or something. Not the sort of bath we've got now, of course, but you know, a clean bath, and... 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Did your mother do this, do you remember? Would she have bathed you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Well, there must have been a stage when she did, but... 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You don't have clear memories of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 No, not clear memories, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 You don't remember your father doing anything like bathing you and putting you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
Oh, no, no. He was out every night. I mean, you see the things that he was mixed up with, you see. It was after the war, actually, but it'll give you an idea of what the Board of Guardians were. My brother, w
ho came out of the Army, he'd got married, had two children and there was a third coming on the way and he used to suffer with this malaria. \{ILLEGIBLE\} night and morning to work at Lake }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11554922 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024  Elliott's foundry. He'd get wet, perhaps, going there, work all day
 in wet clothes; anyway, he died of pneumonia with this child on the way. So has wife, this poor widow, was left with 2 children and one to come, well, 3 children, you could say. I think she had - I'm not sure if she had a pension of about seven shillings
,
 but she applied to the Board of Guardians and they said, 'oh, well, you must go back to work at the factory'. 'Oh,' she said, 'I can't. I can't leave my 3 children.' 'Can't you get somebody to look after them?' She said, 'I can't pay anybody to look afte
r
 my children, I just can't afford it, and I'm not leaving my children, anyway'. They said, 'well, you can't expect us to give you anything. Anyway, you go outside and think about it, and come back and tell us whether you're going back to the factory'. And
 
she went outside, and come back and they said, 'well, have you made up your mind?' She said, 'yes, I'm not leaving my children'. And eventually they said, 'well, we'll allow you 5/- for 3 months, but in the meantime you'd better get a job. So she had this
 5/- and then she did a little work at a public house, you see, housework.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 That would have been 5/- a month would it have been, that she got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 A week, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 A week, for 3 months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I assume that. My sister told me this story. And, she w
ouldn't go back to work, she did this little job at the public house, you know, cleaning up during the day. She used to wear... put a little cloth over her head, as women did, and one day she come out into the street and just crossed to the shop over the 
road and a man named \{BLANK\}
 who was the representative of the Board of Guardians, you see, was waiting and he saw her. 'Ah, caught you now, then, haven't I! You're at work. And what do you earn?' She said, 'a shilling'. 'Oh, well that'll be stopped'. And s
he worried whether the woman where she worked would say... if he went there, what she would say, but it so happened that the woman said a shilling. But anyway, so she was stopped this shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Stopped off her 5/-, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Off her 5/-, yes. I m
ean, that just gives you an idea what the Board of Guardians... when I refer to the Board of Guardians when me father was on... 'cos he used to try \{ILLEGIBLE\} my friend, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Mr.
{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}Wash{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} rather thought of these people... and they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \ul\insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024  in some ways decent people, you see. They were not of the same breed, and they'd not consider... But we were like a breed of animal, you see. But that was after 1918, of course, because me brother was back from the war.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 But still, that sort of thing would have happened in 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
If it was like that, you can bet what it was like earlier on. And my father, as I say, when he got on the Board of Guardians and he was, like, the sole representative of these old ladies \{ILLEGIBLE\} I can't remember details now, but he would come home
, you know, with his tales of \{ILLEGIBLE\} and these poor it dears, you know, with their questions.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497673 K  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 Extract of letter from R. Spurgeon, 150 Berick Road, Halstead, Essex - to Mrs. T. Thompson, dated 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\super\insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024  November, 1969.
\par First, the two penny gaff, I hav
e never seen this in print, but I am sure this must be correct. Then the pads, a pad was from a flat piece of dough, cut in a rectangle, or triangle. These baked up very light and fluffy, some bakers used to deliver them hot for breakfast. I think you can
 still buy them.
\par My mother when she was about 8 years old, would have to do straw braiding or plaiting after school. This was for basket work, or straw hats for horses to keep the sun off their heads. I suppose you have never seen these.
\par She had to do a certain number before she went to bed.
\par When she left school she went into service, living in. Later she had lodgings in Halstead and worked at the mill as a weaver.
\par At first weaving crepe which I think was the sort of material that women wore for veils, particularly the black veil for morning. Later weaving silk, I should think weaving them was quite a skilled job.
\par My sister Lucy was a weaver. She got marry during the war, but I think her husband was a foundry labourer before the war, and a butcher after.
\par Vera was also a weaver. Her husband was one of a family of painters and decorators. The whole family were very talented, the father and five sons could all paint pictures, including portraits. Her husband was killed in the war.
\par My brother Aldis passed the exam
ination at school and was allowed to leave at 12 years. Started work at a Tailor's shop at 3/6 per week, then moved to a fishmongers at 5/-. From then he took a job as gardener at one of the big houses at 12/-. Later when he wanted to marry he moved to "C
olne Priory" as under gardener at 17/6. From then to \{BLANK\} and \{BLANK\} Foundry at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Braintree{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} as an \{ILLEGIBLE\}
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7350282\charrsid11999024 My sister Erica}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
 who gave me most of this information started as nursemaid at 1/6d. per week, increased to 2/-. Later she also became a weaver at the mill. She married a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Cumberland{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} man who was stationed in Halstead with the army during the war. Before going in the Army he was a groom and gardener in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Cumberland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par My brother Beverly started at a bakers in Halstead and later as a baker in Tiptree living in and cycling home at weekends. In 1914 he joined the army as a baker in the A.S.C. Later transferred to infantry. This brings us up to 1918.
\par 
\par Letter from Mr. Spurgeon, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}150 Beridge Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, Halstead. 1.12.69.
\par I have had another session with my sisters Hilda, Erica, and will try to answer your other questions.
\par With regard to Lucy, I made a mistake in telling you she did not get married until after the war. I am now informed that she got married while her man was home on leave after being wounded. He went back
 to the Front and was wounded again, with shrapnel in this thigh. This could not be removed as it was in or near the bone, and the eventually became disabled. He had no pension and I remember getting up at a Conservative meeting to ask for an interview wi
th R.A.B. Butler after the meeting. He took the matter up with the Minister of Pensions, but we were informed that because of a three year clause it was too late to claim. From this time until he died he had to rely on Public Assistance.
\par Lucy continued to work as a weaver during and after the war. For a time after the war, Lucy lived at home with us and her husband lived with his people until they got a cottage at White Colne near his work.
\par She then gave up work and started a family.
\par VERA left the mill before her husband was killed and took in two loders, and did some domestic work. She received a pension of 17/6 increased to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11554922 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 1. Later she got married again. Her and husband was a turner at the Foundry, but they soon got a job as Caretakers at the local {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Girls
{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Grammar School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, with a House. She remained here until she died.
\par ALDIS, I made a mistake in telling you he was a \{ILLEGIBLE\}, he was in fact an acetylene welder. He continued this until his death.
\par My sister Hilda Erica, continued to work as a weaver for a f
ew years after she was married. She had a son, who she used to bring to our house for mother to look after while she went to work. Her husband got a job as Foundry Storekeeper when he left the Army, but he did not like the Foundry, and got a job as Groom 
and Gardener until he retired.
\par BEVERLEY was in the Balkans, mainly {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Greece{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 during the war, and contracted malaria. When he left the Army he had a pension of 6/- a week, but this was later stopped. He got a job at Lake and Elliots, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Braintree
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, as an Electric Welder. This meant commuting to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Braintree{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 by cycle each day, after getting wet through, as his health was already undermined, he soon got pneumonia and died. His widow was left with two small children and one on the way. She had a widows pension of 25/- per
 week, to keep herself and the 3 children.
\par 
\par This of course, was not enough and she had to apply to the Board of Guardians for relief. These people tried to browbeat her into going back to her job at the mill, but she refused to leave her three small childr
en. They eventually granted her 5/- per week for four weeks, but expected her to be back at her old job by this time. She did not go back to the factory, and they continued to pay the 5/-. She tried to earn a few shillings by doing some cleaning at a near
b
y Public House, for which she received 2/6d, but one day when she left the house, the relieving officer was waiting for her (probably tipped off by some other poor woman who wanted the job) he said I have caught you this time, and asked what she was paid,
 
and then checked with the woman of the house. He told her that she would be stopped by that amount, but she told him she would not because she would not do the job any more, which she did not. She also sometimes made a pair boys trousers including lining 
for 4d a pair. People would bring an old coat for her to make the trousers from. As her three boys grew up, they helped her. She recently died of cancer.
\par ALEC left school and worked at a brewery. By the time he was 16 years old he was driving the Brewery lo
rry. He then became a bus driver for several years. Later, he got a job in the Dying Department at Courtaulds, Bocking. He is still in this job, but is now Chargehand. My wife has had no job other than teaching.
\par I have a younger sister Beatrice who refused to work at the factory and did domestic work until she got married. She is now a widow.
\par I hope I have given you the information you need.
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s15\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid14497673 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 I told {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Mr.{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}Wash{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 I had received your letter, and he said he had not answered yours yet. I think he will. He has not be
en ill, but something much more exciting, he has got married to a widow. They are very happy together. Instead of being on his own, he now has her children and grandchildren calling regularly and many other relations. This is probably why he has no}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4072932 t written yet.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8728896\charrsid11999024 
\par }}